HEADWORD: Thirdings
<hw>Third"ings</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <fld>(Eng.
Law)</fld> <def>The third part of the corn or grain growing on the
ground at the tenant's death, due to the lord for a heriot, as within
the manor of Turfat in Herefordshire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thirdly</ent>⟦br⟧
